    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Book demos with Google Calendar and Twilio\n\n**Pattern:** Meeting Scheduling · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nBook demos with Google Calendar and Twilio. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual booking is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Booking Form Submission → Check Calendar Availability → Slot Free? → Create Calendar Event → Send Confirmation (Twilio) → Hold Until Reminder Time → Send Reminder (Twilio) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to meeting scheduling without manual effort\n- Anyone automating booking in healthcare\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Improves response time\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; Twilio SID + token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "7be91bda-aa66-3326-68be-42f03e7620c0",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "21764d16-21bd-3ffc-239a-7eb7f279282e",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your booking process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
